headline: How Williams’ $3.1 Billion Bet on Data Center Power Will Impact WMB Investors
summary: Williams Companies recently announced a US$3.1 billion investment in two power projects designed to supply electricity to data centers in grid-constrained regions, secured by long-term agreements with a major investment-grade customer. This move raises the company's total capital committed to power innovation to about US$5 billion, highlighting Williams' increased focus on supporting emerging demand from AI and digital infrastructure.
